news.title: UltraTech Cement slapped with two GST demand orders totalling Rs 72 lakh
news.para: It has received an order from Assistant Commissioner, Bathinda, for a demand of "Rs 25.11 lakh together with interest and penalty, alleging that the ISD (Input Service Distributor) credit not reflected" in the statement of FY18, the Aditya Birla Group firm said in a regulatory filing on Friday.

news.title: Australian home prices surged 8% in 2023 but rates, inflation cloud outlook
news.para: Figures from property consultant CoreLogic out on Tuesday showed prices nationally jumped 8.1% in 2023, but well below the 24.5% surge recorded in 2021. Prices in December nudged higher by 0.4%, the smallest monthly gain since February.

news.title: Property registration in Mumbai rises 4% to record 1,26,907 units in 2023: Report
news.para: The registration number hit a record in 2023, beating the previous high of 1,22,035 units in the previous year, real estate consultant Knight Frank India data showed.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's sales up 6% to 27.3 million tonnes in Q3 FY24
news.para: UltraTech Cement's grey cement production in the domestic market was at 25.44 MT in the October-December quarter FY24, reporting 5 per cent growth, while its white cement production was 0.48 MT, up 14 per cent.

news.title: Housing sales in Gurugram up 13% in 2023; down 7-8% each in Noida, Greater Noida: Anarock
news.para: Real estate consultant Anarock's data showed that sales of residential properties in Gurugram went up 13 per cent to 36,970 in 2023 from 32,615 units in the previous year.

news.title: UAE government to help Kerala set up tourism township in hills
news.para: It is unclear at this point if there will be direct involvement of the UAE government or whether the UAE government is only a facilitator for participation by private companies.

news.title: Haryana sports department pays Rs 2.2 crore pending property tax to Panchkula civic body
news.para: Panchkula municipal corporation officials said in the last nine months, the civic body has recovered a record property tax of Rs 17.05 crore. The campaign launched by MC to collect property tax cast a major impact, they claimed.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram smart city road works to be completed by April
news.para: The minister who visited and evaluated the construction works of roads included in the Smart City project in the city on Sunday said that 38 roads under the Kerala Road Fund Board has been chosen for maintenance and revamp under the Smart City project.

news.title: Secunderabad Cantonment draft policy to halt illegal digging of borewells
news.para: This is being done to arrest illegal digging of borewells and extracting groundwater indiscriminately, sid SCB officials adding that the Board has formulated a comprehensive policy with all these regulations.

news.title: Delhi government releases Rs 150 crore for construction of two RRTS corridors
news.para: While Rs 100 crore is for Delhi-Shahjahanpur-Neemrana-Behror line, the remaining amount will be spent on the Delhi-Panipat corridor.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body to serve notices to property tax defaulters soon
news.para: Chandigarh municipal corporation might go ahead and attach properties of property tax defaulters if they don’t clear the dues.

news.title: Greater Noida authority to lease unsold flats to government employees
news.para: The move will help the GNIDA generate revenue and address the housing crisis among government staffers, said officials.

news.title: John Abraham buys bungalow in Mumbai's Khar for over Rs 70.83 crore
news.para: The bungalow, 372 Nirmal Bhavan, boasts an expansive total built-up area of 5,416 square feet, spanning across the ground floor and two additional levels. Notably, the actor has acquired this property through a transaction involving a total of 10 sellers, all of whom are members of the same family.

news.title: Pune: Drone use by DCB boosts property tax collection to 6.5 crore
news.para: “Our annual property tax revenue was Rs 1.8 crore earlier. But now, using an effective drone survey, the revenue has increased to Rs 6.5 crore,” Amit Mane, defence estate officer of Pune Circle, told TOI. It must be noted that the cantonment is spread across 9,500 acres.

news.title: Mumbai: Property tax bills uploaded by BMC citing 'hike' send citizens into tizzy
news.para: A footnote in the bill cited the Court had held three rules of the Capital Valuation rules as invalid and also stated that the bills were being issued as a security/adhoc basis and that the civic body reserved the right to reassess the properties with retrospective effect and collect tax accordingly after announcement of a revised policy on assessment.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body collects Rs 2 crore property tax on December 30
news.para: ​Till now, around 85,000 property tax returns have been filed by residents under the OTS policy and the civic body has generated revenue of around Rs 10 crore.

news.title: Assam CM set to inaugurate country’s biggest PMAY colony in Dibrugarh
news.para: The sprawling colony, nestled on 32 bighas of land within the serene environs of Namsang tea estate near the Assam-Arunachal border, is being constructed at an estimated cost of Rs 4 crore.

news.title: Consumer forum orders Vadodara civic body to repair flats, give amenities
news.para: VMC constructed Nurm Awas on the Ajwa Road, but the residents found that the construction was of very poor quality. They raised their grievances and made frequent representations before the civic authorities.

news.title: Maharashtra CM lays foundation stone for cluster development at Wagle estate
news.para: This phase of cluster development is proposed at the MIDC plot F-2 which is being undertaken by the Thane Municipal corporation as well as Cidco.

news.title: Delhi civic body holds 60 drives, demolishes 111 illegal structures in December
news.para: As per data provided by MCD, between December 1 and 30, at least 111 illegal structures were demolished in different zones across the city. A total of 60 demolition drives were held. Shahdara North and South, followed by Narela and South witnessed maximum such drives.
